{{Other people|Bibhutibhushan|Bibhutibhushan (disambiguation){{!}}Bibhutibhushan}} {{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=November 2018}} {{Infobox writer <!-- For more information see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]]. --> | name = Bibhutibhushan Mukhopadhyay | image = BibhutibhushanMukhopadhyayPic.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date|df=yes|1894|10|24}} | birth_place = [[Darbhanga district]], [[Bihar]], [[British India]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|df=yes|1987|07|29|1894|10|24}} | death_place = India | occupation = Poet, novelist, playwright, essayist | language = [[Bengali language|Bengali]], English | nationality = | education = | alma_mater = | period = | genre = | subject = | movement = | notableworks = | spouse = | children = | relatives = | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | portaldisp = | influences = | influenced = }}
''' Bibhutibhushan Mukhopadhyay''' (24 October 1894 – 29 July 1987) was a [[Bengali language|Bengali]] author.
==Life== Bibhutibhushan Mukhopadhyay was born on 24 October 1894 in Pandoul, a village of the Mithila region of [[British India]].{{citation needed|date=June 2018}}
He received the [[Ananda Puraskar]] award in 1958, the [[Rabindra Puraskar]] in 1972 and the [[Sharatchandra Puraskar]] in 1978. He was also awarded the [[Jagattarini Puraskar]] from [[Calcutta University]], a D.Litt degree from the [[University of Burdwan]] and [[Desikottama]] from the [[Visva-Bharati University]] of [[Shantiniketan]].{{citation needed|date=June 2018}}
Mukhopadhyay died on 29 July 1987 in [[Darbhanga]] at the age of 93, He never married.{{citation needed|date=June 2018}}
==Works== Bibhutibhushan Mukhopadhyay’s first book, ''Ranur Prothom Vagh'' was published in 1934. His writings were included in the academic curriculae in Bihar, Bengal and [[Bangladesh]].{{citation needed|date=June 2018}}
