There are no nasal vowels.

Like other [[Abugida|alphasyllabaries]], Devanagari writes out syllables by adding vowel [[diacritic]]s to consonant bases. The table below includes all the vowel symbols used in Marathi, along with a transliteration of each sound into [[Latin script]] and [[International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]].

