A defining feature of the Marathi language is the frequent substitution of the consonant ल (la) in Sanskrit words with the [[retroflex lateral flap]] ळ ({{IAST|ḷa}}). For instance, कुळ (''{{IAST|kuḷa}}'') for the Sanskrit कुलम् (''kulam'' 'clan') and कमळ (''{{IAST|kamaḷ}}'') for Sanskrit कमलम् (''kamalam'' 'lotus'). ळ is possibly an import in Marathi from Dravidian languages, although it may also have originated from [[Vedic Sanskrit]].

