{{Wiktionary|revival}}

A '''revival''' is a restaging of a [[stage (theatre)|stage]] production after its original run has closed.  New material may be added. A [[feature film|filmed]] version is said to be an adaptation and requires writing of a [[screenplay]]. Revivals are common in [[Broadway theatre]].

