{{italic title}}
The '''Épinal-Erfurt glossary''' is a glossary of terms.  It consists of two manuscripts (Épinal and Erfurt), and contains terms in Old English.<ref>{{cite book|last=Pheifer|first=J. D.|title=Old English Glosses in the Épinal-Erfurt Glossary|publisher=Oxford University Press|year=1974|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books/about/Old_English_glosses_in_the_%C3%89pinal_Erfur.html?id=kN5ZAAAAMAAJ}}</ref>

It has been described as "The earliest body of written English",<ref name="brown">{{cite journal|last1=Brown|first1=Alan K.|title=Reviewed Work: Old English Glosses in the Epinal-Erfurt Glossary by J. D. Pheifer|journal=Speculum|date=October 1977|volume=52|issue=4|pages=1031–1037|doi=10.2307/2855442|jstor=2855442}}</ref> and is thought to have been compiled at [[Malmesbury]] for [[Aldhelm]] (c. 639-709).<ref name="godden">{{cite book|last1=Gretsch|first1=Mechthild|editor1-last=Godden|editor1-first=Malcolm|editor2-last=Lapidge|editor2-first=Michael|title=The Cambridge Companion to Old English Literature|date=2013|publisher=CUP|isbn=9780521193320|page=278|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=Gyh6gPccWx4C&lpg=PA292&ots=ZxA8tbiDkg&dq=%22epinal%20erfurt%20glossary%22%20aldhelm&pg=PA278#v=onepage&q=%22epinal%20erfurt%20glossary%22%20aldhelm&f=false|chapter=Literacy and the uses of the vernacular}}</ref>

Two manuscripts of the Glossary exist today: one in the Bibliothèque Municipale of [[Épinal]], France, which was written in [[Southumbria]] in the last quarter of the 7th century and one in the Wissenschaftliche Allgemeinbibliothek of [[Erfurt]], Germany, written at [[Cologne Cathedral]] in the first half of the 9th century.<ref name="lapidge">{{cite book|last1=Lapidge|first1=Michael|authorlink1=Michael Lapidge|editor1-last=Godden|editor1-first=Malcolm|editor2-last=Keynes|editor2-first=Simon|editor1-link=Malcolm Godden|editor2-link=Simon Keynes|title=Anglo Saxon England: Vol 36|date=2008|publisher=Cambridge UP|isbn=9780521883436|page=35|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=i3s1Q4XXIF8C&lpg=PA35&ots=cvAAmx71x1&dq=%22epinal%20erfurt%20glossary%22&pg=PA34#v=onepage&q=%22epinal%20erfurt%20glossary%22&f=false|chapter=The Career of Aldhelm}}</ref>

[[Henry Sweet]] published an edition of the Glossary in 1885 in ''The Oldest English Texts'' ([[Early English Text Society]]), reprinted in 1938, 1957 and 1966. J. D. Pheifer published ''Old English Glosses in the Epinal-Erfurt Glossary'' ([[Clarendon Press]], {{ISBN|0198111649}}) in 1974.<ref name=brown />

